From: Egbert Eich <eich@suse.de>
Date: Tue Feb  7 19:53:48 CET 2012
Subject: [PATCH] drm/i915/sdvo: Fix up EDID matching logic.
Patch-mainline: To be mainlined.
Refrences: bnc #744315

Remove duplicate test for LVDS which works against the logic in
intel_sdvo_connector_matches_edid(): if EDID type and connector
type match assume a monitor is connected.

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_sdvo.c |    8 ++------
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

--- a.orig/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_sdvo.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/i915/intel_sdvo.c
@@ -1374,13 +1374,9 @@ intel_sdvo_detect(struct drm_connector *
 		if (edid != NULL) {
 			if (intel_sdvo_connector_matches_edid(intel_sdvo_connector,
 							      edid))
-				ret = IS_LVDS(intel_sdvo_connector) ?
-					connector_status_disconnected :
-					connector_status_connected;
+				ret = connector_status_connected;
 			else
-				ret = IS_LVDS(intel_sdvo_connector) ?
-					connector_status_connected :
-					connector_status_disconnected;
+				ret = connector_status_disconnected;
 
 			connector->display_info.raw_edid = NULL;
 			kfree(edid);
